sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1404001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Ptac-NiCoTB-rcn-csgBAEFG, turns E. coli into a functional Ni and Co biofilter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part, when expressed in a rcnA E. coli strain, allows the formation of a functional Ni2+ and Co2+ biofilter capturing up to 3 mg of metal per g of bacterial dry weight when exposed to 20 ??M Ni2+ or Co2+, in only 10 mn. This is one of the best performances and the fastest reported until now.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Alexandre Duprey

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K540000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: rcn-csgBAEFG, over-induces adherence in response to cobalt
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This parts associates the rcn promoter, whose expression increases with cobalt or nickel in the medium, with csgBAEFG, an operon that enables the production and secretion of curlis, which are adherent proteins. With this part, strains can become adherent in response to cobalt or nickel in the medium.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Melanie Geffroy, Philippe Thomas
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Direct synthesis from Genecust, using the sequence of the genes as found in E.Coli MC4100 genome.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Several internal iGEM restriction sites were initially present in the genes : EcoR1 in csgEFG, Pst1 in csgBA and rcn. They were eliminated in such a way that it does not affect the expression of the genes.
